    "name": "Stream Pilot API",
    "description": "Stream Pilot NestJS API — health, auth (JWT cookie), dashboard analytics, productions + run sheets, crew/equipment resources, and push notifications.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import `stream-pilot.postman_environment.json` (optional) or use collection variables.\n2. Set `baseUrl` to `http://localhost:3001` (direct API) or `http://localhost:3000/api` (via Next.js proxy).\n3. Run **Auth → Register** or **Auth → Login** first — Postman stores the `token` httpOnly cookie automatically.\n4. Run **Dashboard → Get Stats** to fetch pipeline analytics.\n5. Run **Productions → Create Production** — saves `productionId` to collection variables. Requires `eventDate`, `startTime`, and `startsAt` (ISO 8601).\n6. Run **Crew → Create Crew Member** and **Equipment → Create Equipment** — saves `crewMemberId` and `equipmentId`.\n7. Run **Assignments → Replace Assignments** — assigns crew and equipment to the production.\n8. Run **Notifications → Get VAPID Public Key** and **Subscribe** to register a push endpoint.\n9. Run **Productions → Update Production** with `\"status\": \"SCHEDULED\"` to create an inbox notification; check **Notifications → List Notifications** and **Unread Count**.\n\n## Auth\nProtected routes require the `token` cookie set by register/login. Postman Cookie Jar must be enabled (default).\n\n## List endpoints\nProductions, crew, and equipment list routes support optional `search`, `sort`, and `order` query params (see each request for allowed sort fields).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
